00:08:48,977 --> 00:08:51,719
Here the events are presented in a laundry list format.

190
00:08:53,321 --> 00:08:57,004
Now by their very nature, our events were designed to fall into different buckets, like

191
00:08:57,144 --> 00:08:59,266
daily, weekly, monthly, and so on.

192
00:08:59,707 --> 00:09:03,510
But tell me, as a player, can you make that out just by looking at the screen?

193
00:09:04,231 --> 00:09:08,095
And that information is important, because different players will engage with different

194
00:09:08,175 --> 00:09:09,916
event types based on their preferences.

195
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:15,301
I may be the kind of player who just likes to play daily events, because that's the kind

196
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:16,642
of time commitment I want to do.

197
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:21,543
But you can see that I cannot make that decision just by looking at the information on the

198
00:09:21,563 --> 00:09:21,823
screen.

199
00:09:23,384 --> 00:09:26,845
If the player clicks on one of the event type, he's brought to screen number three, where

200
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:31,126
you can see some more information about the rewards, some call to actions, and access

201
00:09:31,146 --> 00:09:31,747
to leaderboards.

202
00:09:32,327 --> 00:09:35,108
If you click on the leaderboard button, you're brought to screen number four.

203
00:09:36,228 --> 00:09:40,230
Here player can see the leaderboard and his position relative to rest of the players in

204
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:40,490
the game.

